<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\lax02_01_iceberg_dungeon\lax02_02_cv_godhmr_illusion_wzd</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>29</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Damn it, why can't I remember?" 

The soul of this robed priestess circles around the same thoughts in a pattern reminiscent of pacing. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You still don't remember the spell?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Farewell."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Didn't come this far just to tuck tail and surrender. Not to them." Unconcerned with you, her spirit persists in rapidly assessing the situation frozen in time.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Give her the Memory of Magranite Incantations.] "I think this is what you're looking for."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I... of course! Simple. How'd I forget a thing like that anyway?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>As she begins the incantation, you comprehend where and how the bomb was hidden. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Knowing this, it feels as if a thousand pairs of eyes are observing your progress at once. The illusion fades under their scrutiny.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You've got to remember the incantation. Don't forget, don't let it go."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Who are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Continue observing her.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>She doesn't seem to hear you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Waidwen's soul is in the bomb? This just got more complicated."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You won't hear this, but I'll return your memory if I happen across it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>The mechanism was elegant in its simplicity. When a fragment of Waidwen reacted to his approach on the bridge above, it conducted soul energy into the copper and triggered the explosive.

A bomb for Waidwen made of Waidwen. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>It was a delicate trigger by design. The work of removing such a critical part will involve no small risk. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can't think... why can't I think of it?" 

Her soul dims its luminosity to a speck, what you take to be the spiritual equivalent of a wince. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>The soul of this priestess is muttering an incantation under her breath.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Once I've got my senses back, I'll drag them all along for my fiery ride into Hel." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Think of a spell, try and help her recall something.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>Her soul twitches, as if your intervention makes a small dent in her confusion, but it isn't enough to restore her memory.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ugh. Almost had it that time." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>No sooner does the book make contact with her than it ceases to exist, absorbed into her memories. You feel the essence of the priestess swell with life and vigor.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I memorized that illusion spell. How can it be gone? Another second and Waidwen will know the bomb is here. Damn it, girl, this is your chance..." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The whole &lt;i&gt;point&lt;/i&gt; of the thing is that his soul finds him first." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you intuit her meaning, you catch a flash of memory:

Robed priests assembling a delicate mechanism - spiked copper plates housing a fragile shard of adra. 

The adra houses a piece of Waidwen's soul. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Durance was right. The bomb worked because a part of Waidwen's soul was inside."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You can't remember the spell to hide the bomb?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's like I'm on stage and forgot the words of the song... how could this happen?" Her soul turns on itself in desperation. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>